yourself</em> for having identified with that energy.</p>

<p>Use your ordinary experience, then, in each day to observe what pushes
your buttons. And if you will stay with it ‚Äî and in just a moment we
will give you a very simple technique for doing so ‚Äî if you can stay
with it, it will reveal to you the energies that are in need of your
forgiveness.</p>

<p>The technique is quite simple. As you go through your day, observe when
you feel as though you are in contraction. Are the muscles of the body
tight? Is the breath very shallow? Does your voice become faster or
louder when you speak about some energy in someone else? That is a sign
that you need to do healing within yourself. When you recognize that
these kinds of signs are going on ‚Äî in other words, life has presented
you with an opportunity to be disturbed ‚Äî that is a sign that there is
something that requires healing.</p>

<p>So therefore, count it a blessing if you feel disturbed. Turn your
awareness from what you think is causing the disturbance and remember
the first axiom:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>I am the source of my experience. I‚Äôm feeling disturbed. What is it in
me that needs to be healed?</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Begin to breathe deeply with the body and rhythmically. Let the body
soften and relax, and ask,</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>What is it within this person‚Äôs energy that is really pushing my button?</p>
</blockquote>

<p>And you will see it right away:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Oh, they‚Äôre so critical. Criticism pushes my buttons. Where have I been
critical of others?</p>
</blockquote>

<p>And it might hit you right away:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Well, I‚Äôm being critical because they‚Äôre critical.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Or memories will come back, distasteful memories, if you‚Äôre judging
